# Axis 9 — nondeterminism (many-resume product)

A `multi effect` whose handler resumes once per choice and combines the results
with `flatMap`, producing the full product of two choice points (§14.1
"many-resume handlers"). The deepest in-process use of reusable resumption: the
continuation after each `pick` is invoked once per option.

```scalascript
multi effect Ch:
  def pick(xs: List[Int]): Int

val r = handle {
  val x = Ch.pick(List(1, 2))
  val y = Ch.pick(List(10, 20))
  x + y
} {
  case Ch.pick(xs, resume) => xs.flatMap(o => resume(o))
}
println(r)
```
